<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title></title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Northumbria University Centre for Forensic Science</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> (FSS016)</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Northumbria University Centre for Forensic Science’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">mission is to conduct influential interdisciplinary research on forensic science theory and practice in order to improve its contribution to criminal justice and the safeguarding of human rights. Its membership consists of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">five</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> members of academic staff including Professors of sociology and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> forensic science, and practitioners who contribute over fifty year</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">s’ </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">professional experience to the Centre</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">’s activities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">. It hosts four full-time postgraduate and postdoctoral researchers, and is supported by Leverhulme Trust, EU Framework 7 and other international research grants and contracts.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:5pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The following comments are offered in response to the request for written evidence. They represent the views of the Centre’s members and are not necessarily those of our employer.</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:6pt 0pt 12pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Does the Government have an effective strategy for forensic science in the UK and is it sufficient to support forensic science R&amp;D and criminal justice</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">?</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The present Government’s measures for forensic science look like an </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">ad hoc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">reaction</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> decision to close the Forensic Science Service</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> (FSS)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">made </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">on</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the basis of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> external drivers. This is not a strategy.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The issues of research and development, and support for criminal justice are complex.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">FSS</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> enjoyed a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> substantial capital and recurrent expenditure budget for research, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">underpinning its </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">output</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">—as measured by publications in peer reviewed international scientific journals, for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> example. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The FSS research budget and facilities would have impressed the science faculties of many research Universities, and it needs to be asked whether the FSS delivered value for money in research—by comparison with a large science department in a research University, for example. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In any event, however, government funding has essentially evaporated and focused research on this scale has ceased. In its place, it is proposed that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the Research Councils (RCUK) and Technology Strategy Board (TSB) fill the vacuum. RCUK, however, have a very disappointing track record whe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">re</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> forensic scie</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nce funding is concerned and it would be naïve to assume this situation will improve significantly. The TSB route may favour near-to-market activities, but</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> not more innovative ones and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> is also yet to be proven.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 39.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.55pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Support for criminal justice presently relies on an evidently unstable commercial market and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> newly-expanded</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> police forensic science </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">laboratory activities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> While it is easy to attribute </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">errors in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> some recent cases—</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the Gareth Williams and Adam Scott cases</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, for example—</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to fundamental</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ly</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">flawed standards and regulation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">y</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">may be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">more </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">superficial</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> consequence of ‘bedding in’ a new structure</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">—</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">indefensible though they may be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 39.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.55pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The subsuming of forensic science back into the police service represents a fundamental risk to the justice system. While the FSS derived its income overwhelmingly from prosecution or police work, it was at least a nominal step away from the investigation and hence had a measure of independence, albeit a small one.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 39.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.55pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The police laboratories handling forensic work prior to the establishment of the FSS were considered too close to investigations and prosecuting authorities. Indeed, o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ne of the reasons the FSS was established was because police laboratories were seen as potential or real causes of wrongful convictions. In this respect, the current measures are a dangerous step back to the days of the Guildford Four, Birmingham Six, Judith Ward and other all too numerous cases of miscarriages of justice.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 39.4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.55pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1.8.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A further substantial threat to the justice system is an overall reduction in the frequency of analysis of physical evidence</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. This may tend to favour the prosecution, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">because</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> it is the result of cost-based measures amounting to a disincentive to search for further evidence which may have the power to exonerate an innocent suspect</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:12pt 0pt 12pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Did the FSS transition and closure run smoothly and within budget?</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:6pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Any answer to this question must be largely subjective as it depends on what is meant by ‘smoothly’ and ‘within budget’. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Inadequate investigation of physical evidence in criminal investigation and miscarriages of justice</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> whether</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">potential or real </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are clearly unacceptable, but given such radical restructuring undertaken in the context of a global economic downturn it might be argued that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the transition</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">—although not without substantial problems—has been relatively smooth as far as the justice system is concerned, and not as disastrous as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">many</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> may have predicted. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Was there</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> ever</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> a budget for closure?</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> The cost of closure may presently exceed the losses the FSS had </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">persistently </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sustained</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, but a more realistic and pragmatic measure of financial probity may be whether forensic science is delivered reliably</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> efficiently, and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">cost-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">effective</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ly</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in the medium term. </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">What impacts have the FSS’s closure had on (i) the criminal justice system and (ii) forensic science R&amp;D and training? In particular, have the appropriate quality standards and accreditation been rigorously maintained? (please provide evidence/examples)</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The Gareth Williams and Adam Scott cases offer evidence that the restructuring of the market has affected the justice system and standards. Equally, however, it may be noted that the FSS also made rather inexcusable errors from time to time and the current difficulties may be more superficial than fundamental.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The restructuring has led to a cost-burden for staff training and retraining, as well as development of new research.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">What should be role of the Forensic Science Regulator?</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The present structure of the Forensic Science Regulator’s Office is fundamental to the on-going problems in the forensic science sector. It lacks independence from the police, affecting both the financial viability of the commercial market</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> (see (5))</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and the judicial impartiality of forensic science service delivery—in particular, via the retrograde step of the reintroduction of poli</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ce laboratories (see (6)) and an overall reduction in testing (see (1)).</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">arket regulation</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and standards and accreditation functions should be separate, and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">entirely independent of the Home Office.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">arket regulation activities should</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> follow the model of other regulatory bodie</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s such as OFWAT, OFTEL or OFCOM and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be responsible for:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-25.2pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.3.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Licencing forensic science service providers</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-25.2pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.3.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Balancing costs to the taxpayer against the need to have a viable market</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-25.2pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.3.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Encouraging investment</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, research</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and innovation</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-25.2pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.3.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Encouraging competition where it benefits the taxpayer and the justice system</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-25.2pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.3.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Balancing the interests of the Home Office against the interests of the provider</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-25.2pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.3.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Ensuring the market works in the interests of justice and the rule of law</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Regulation accreditation of forensic science practices should be conducted by another independent body that might be likened to the Drinking Water Inspectorate and might be called the Forensic Science Inspectorate. It is important that this body has the authority to be proactive in ensuring ethical and effective use of forensic science technology and procedures.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Forensic science standards and proficiency testing should be the responsibility a third body. It might be subsumed within the wider</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> activities of a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> scientific standards and proficiency testing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> body similar, for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">example, to the US National Institute of Standards and Technology, which is part of the US Department of Commerce.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Presently LGC, a commercial company, undertakes many such activities in the UK.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The body responsible market regulation might be called OFFOR. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">OFFOR would hear representation from the Home Office / Police, the forensic science service providers, and the Forensic Science Inspectorate (who would in turn ensure providers meet independent scientific and proficiency standards).</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">What is the size of the forensics market and how stable is it?</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We estimate the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">xternal forensic market </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">(</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> work done by non-police forensic suppliers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> was running at about £170 million per annum until about 2010.  The market </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">then </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">shrank rapidly</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ACPO were suggesting </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> likely</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">external market of £110 million </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in the years following</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> FSS closure</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> suggest that the curr</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ent market is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> a lot</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> smaller than this—</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">possibly around £</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">60</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> million. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Home Office tendering mechanism </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">pushes</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> providers to be even more competitive</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> on price and it is questionable</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> whether the provision of forensic science to the UK is financially viable</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> under Home Office policy</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">While</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> police provision </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">may appear</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> cheaper</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, substantial costs—for buildings, utilities, management and capital costs—may be hidden, and ACPO appears to be unable to cost these expenses, which will be considerable.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The closure of the FSS and unpredictability of the outcome of tenders for regional contracts have badly affected financial viability and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">staff complements—cycles of recruitment and redundancy—</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of forensic science providers.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">How are forensic science services procured by police forces and could procurement processes be improved?</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The present procurement structure favours driving down police costs at the expense of stability, investment, innovation and judicial probity. This may risk favouring internal institutional agendas over the rule of law. The structure </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">could </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> better</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> organized</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, such as</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> according to the model outlined in (4) above, for example</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, or some other viable model</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Has the closure of the FSS resulted in a loss of intellectual wealth through its scientists leaving the forensic science profession, or the UK? (please provide evidence/examples)</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The closure of the FSS has dispersed its staff. Many former FSS forensic scientists find themselves in employment with the commercial forensic science providers and in the newly-expanded police laboratories</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, only to find themselves subject to further retrenchments. O</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">thers have collaborated to establish bureaux services</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and a very</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> small number have joined the University sector</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">any have left the profession altogether.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Again, the question invites a subjective response. What exactly is meant by ‘a loss of intellectual wealth’? Undoubtedly, many experienced forensic scientists have left the profession, but not all of them, and although somewhat diminished a wealth of knowledge—it might be argued—remains in the system.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> The ‘institutional’ knowledge of the FSS is undoubtedly lost.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">One place known to develop, nurture and disseminate knowledge is the University. The FSS might have taken a more constructive role in fostering forensic science as peer science in the academy in order that a ‘wealth of knowledge’ might have been developed and sustained more widely</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in the first place</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> In future, better integration of the policing, commercial and academic research is necessary, and an academic sector could provide expertise independent of the commercial market as and when required.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.25pt; padding-left:4.75pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Are current arrangements for the FSS’s archives satisfactory? How could arrangements for the retention of case files and forensic materials in the UK be improved?</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 8.5pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">8.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The overall arrangements are quite unsatisfactory. Piecemeal storage of evidence in the FSS archive and in the archives of individual police services </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">may</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> lead to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">physical</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> deterioration, mix-ups and loss. The uncertainty regarding the organisation of the forensic science market and the structure of police services and police laboratories indicates on-going archiving of evidence should be insulated from inevitable further changes and restructuring. There is a propensity for evidence to ‘go missing’ in investigations of police malpractic</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">8.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">It is essential that physical evidence is archived centrally, securely and independently. Such measures are also essential for proper investigation of cold cases, use of as yet unanticipated new technologies, and potential developments in national or international legal frameworks.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 8.5pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 8.5pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-8.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">January 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 8.5pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-8.5pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>